column5: My son and I got down to the Inner Bay at long Point yesterday. Good day, action was non stop.Brought home 17 keepers.
Nice, did you measure that one in his right hand, that looks like an awesome size for the bay?!!
I did,it was 14inches. I dont normally keep those hogs but she took a jiggin rap deep. She came out of no where and just slammed my lure.I thought it was a smallie the way it fought.
Awesome!!  I love when the bigger ones come flying in and attack like a pike!!
maybe its a peacock bass? its big enough to be one.. nice catch!!!
wow,that's quite the perch. Nice going guys!
